# Vitest layout

- Root `vitest.config.ts` is a **workspace** with `vitest.unit.config.ts`, `vitest.integration.config.ts`, and **`vitest.ui.config.ts`**.
- **File naming** (picks the Vitest project via `include`; no `testNamePattern`):
  - **Unit**: `**/*.unit.test.ts` ‚Äî in-memory / mocked services and repositories.
  - **Integration**: `**/*.integration.test.ts` ‚Äî Postgres + `getIntegration*` wiring from `src/tests/integration.ts`.
  - **UI**: `**/*.ui.test.tsx` ‚Äî React Testing Library + **jsdom** (see below).
- **`pnpm test:unit`** / **`pnpm test:integration`** / **`pnpm test:ui`** run the matching project only.
- **`pnpm test`** runs **`vitest run`** (default **`vitest.config.ts`** workspace: **unit**, **integration**, and **ui** projects). Each project **`include`**s only its glob, so every file runs in exactly one project (no duplicate runs, no `testNamePattern` skips). Integration uses Postgres **`globalSetup`** (`maxWorkers` / `maxConcurrency` **1**). The **ui** project sets **`environment: "jsdom"`** in **`vitest.ui.config.ts`**. **`jsdom`** is pinned to **24.x** (`package.json`): **jsdom 29** currently breaks Vitest‚Äôs test workers (`ERR_REQUIRE_ESM` from `html-encoding-sniffer` ‚Üí `@exodus/bytes`). Revisit the pin when Vitest/jsdom fix that chain.
- **`vitest.integration.config.ts`** sets **`maxWorkers: 1`** and **`maxConcurrency: 1`**: a single Testcontainers Postgres is shared; tests reset data with `truncateTestDb()` in `afterEach`, so parallel tests would race.

# UI / component tests (React Testing Library)

- **`vitest.ui.config.ts`**: **`environment: "jsdom"`**, **`include`**: `**/*.ui.test.tsx`, **`setupFiles`**: `src/tests/vitest-rtl-setup.ts`.
- **Setup**: `src/tests/vitest-rtl-setup.ts` ‚Äî `@testing-library/jest-dom/vitest` + **`cleanup`** in `afterEach` (referenced from **`vitest.ui.config.ts`** only).
- Prefer **role / accessible name** queries matching real `aria-*` labels from the component.

# Integration tests (database)

- **Global setup**: `vitest.integration.global-setup.ts` starts Postgres (Testcontainers), runs migrations, and `project.provide("integrationDatabaseUrl", uri)` for workers. It calls **`register()`** from **`tsx/esm/api`** so Kysely‚Äôs migration loader can `import()` `.ts` files without setting **`NODE_OPTIONS`** on the test script.
- **`src/tests/db.ts`**: `getTestDb()` (lazy singleton using `inject("integrationDatabaseUrl")` from Vitest), `truncateTestDb()`, `migrateTestDb()` used from global setup.
- **`src/tests/integration.ts`**: production-like wiring ‚Äî `SetsRepository(bionicleSets)` plus real repositories on `getTestDb()`. Add **`getIntegration*`** factories here instead of ad-hoc wiring in each test file.
- **Assertions**: prefer **repository methods** (e.g. `getUserRatings`) over raw Kysely queries in tests.
- Put integration specs in **`*.integration.test.ts`** files. Assign services/repos in **`beforeAll`**, not at module top level or in the `describe` callback body before hooks run (avoids calling `inject` / `getTestDb()` when the integration context is not active). Keep **`afterEach` ‚Üí `truncateTestDb()`**.

# Docker and Testcontainers (including WSL)

- Integration and full `pnpm test` need a working container runtime. If you see **"Could not find a working container runtime strategy"**, verify **`docker ps`** works as the same OS user that runs Vitest.
- **`permission denied`** on `docker ps`: add the user to the **`docker`** group (`sudo usermod -aG docker $USER`), then start a new login session (or `wsl --shutdown` from Windows). With **Docker Desktop**, enable **WSL integration** for your distro and keep Docker Desktop running.
- If the socket is not at `/var/run/docker.sock`, set **`DOCKER_HOST`** (e.g. `unix:///path/to/docker.sock`) or use Testcontainers‚Äô **`.testcontainers.properties`** / **`tc.host`** ‚Äî see [testcontainers-node](https://github.com/testcontainers/testcontainers-node) docs. (Optional: a small side-effect module imported from `vitest.integration.config.ts` can probe common Docker Desktop socket paths and set `DOCKER_HOST` before Testcontainers loads.)

# Unit test helpers

- **`src/tests/unit.ts`**: mocks (`*RepositoryMock`, etc.) and unit-test service factories; import from here for **`*.unit.test.ts`** files.
- **`src/tests/fixtures.ts`**: shared fixtures (e.g. `setFixture`).

# Context loaders (shared repository reads)

- If **several services** repeat the **same sequence of repository calls** (often a `Promise.all`) to assemble a **bundle of data** used the same way (e.g. a ‚Äúsnapshot‚Äù for mapping to view models or scoring), **extract** that orchestration into a **small injectable class**‚Äîoften named `*ContextLoader` with a method like `load(...)` returning a typed object. Keeps services focused on domain flow and gives tests one place to mock or integration-test the bundle.
- **Unit tests**: add a **factory** in `src/tests/unit.ts` that builds the loader from repository mocks (with optional `Partial<Port>` overrides), same as other service factories.
- **Integration tests**: add **`getIntegration‚Ä¶`** wiring in `src/tests/integration.ts` next to the other factories, and cover the **meaningful branches** of `load` (e.g. missing vs present user id, optional query options). Example in-repo: `set-view-model.context-loader.integration.test.ts`.
